<p>I would like to rotate a rectangle when e.g. y position achieve specified position. I would like to behave a rectangle as a car on a junction - just turn e.g. right. I prefer just rotate and continue. </p>  <p>A draft code looks like that:</p>  <pre><code>Graphics2D g2d = (Graphics2D) g.create(); g2d.setPaint(new Color(150, 150, 0));  //1. when rectangle achieve 500 on y dimension just rotate left/right if(y==500) {     _rotate = true;     g2d.rotate(Math.toRadians(90.)); } if(_rotate) { //if rotate, continue way on x dimension     ++x ;     g2d.fillRect(x, y, 20, 40); } else { //else go to the north     --y;     g2d.fillRect(x, y, 20, 40); } </code></pre>